Note:
This file implements annotation-block parsing for the Runa frontend.

Runa annotation blocks are first-class machine-parseable constructs (NOT
comments). Each block opens with an "@" marker followed by an annotation
keyword, runs through a colon and an arbitrary body of content tokens, and
closes with a matching "@End <Keyword>" terminator. The bodies carry
developer/architect intent (reasoning, implementation notes, performance
hints, security scope, test cases, etc.) per the Runa annotation system
specification.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Recognize each annotation block opener ("@" followed by an annotation
  keyword from the specification).
- Capture the block's content text between the opening colon and the
  matching "@End <Keyword>" terminator.
- Build an AST annotation node (node_type AST_AI_ANNOTATION) carrying the
  annotation kind, the annotation name string, and the captured content.
- Enforce the "@End" closer requirement: an unterminated annotation block is
  a parse error.
- Support nested and sequential annotation blocks attached to a construct.

This file is a pure PARSER. It contains NO AI service dependency. AI-driven
code generation that consumes annotation intent is a separate, higher-level
tooling/runtime subsystem; it is not part of frontend parsing. The parser's
sole responsibility is to turn annotation source text into faithful AST
annotation nodes for downstream tools to interpret.

Dependencies:
- Imports parser.runa for parser state and the canonical token accessors.
- Imports ast.runa for AST node creation and the canonical node accessors.
- Imports memory/layout.runa for raw structure field access (parser/token
  layout is owned by parser.runa's accessors; raw access is used only where
  no accessor exists).
- Imports collections/list.runa for child-node lists.
- Imports core/string_core.runa and core/string_primitive.runa for string
  construction and comparison.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/ast.runa" as AST
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrimitive

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotation System Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Annotation kind constants. Each corresponds to one specification block.
Note: These are stored in the annotation node's value_type field so downstream
Note: tooling can dispatch on the kind without re-parsing the name string.
Constant ANNOTATION_REASONING as Integer is 1
Constant ANNOTATION_IMPLEMENTATION as Integer is 2
Constant ANNOTATION_UNCERTAINTY as Integer is 3
Constant ANNOTATION_REQUEST_CLARIFICATION as Integer is 4
Constant ANNOTATION_KNOWLEDGE_REFERENCE as Integer is 5
Constant ANNOTATION_TEST_CASES as Integer is 6
Constant ANNOTATION_RESOURCE_CONSTRAINTS as Integer is 7
Constant ANNOTATION_SECURITY_SCOPE as Integer is 8
Constant ANNOTATION_EXECUTION_MODEL as Integer is 9
Constant ANNOTATION_PERFORMANCE_HINTS as Integer is 10
Constant ANNOTATION_PROGRESS as Integer is 11
Constant ANNOTATION_FEEDBACK as Integer is 12
Constant ANNOTATION_TRANSLATION_NOTE as Integer is 13
Constant ANNOTATION_ERROR_HANDLING as Integer is 14
Constant ANNOTATION_TASK as Integer is 15
Constant ANNOTATION_REQUIREMENTS as Integer is 16
Constant ANNOTATION_VERIFY as Integer is 17
Constant ANNOTATION_REQUEST as Integer is 18
Constant ANNOTATION_CONTEXT as Integer is 19
Constant ANNOTATION_COLLABORATION as Integer is 20
Constant ANNOTATION_ITERATION as Integer is 21
Constant ANNOTATION_CLARIFICATION as Integer is 22

Note: AST node type for a parsed annotation block (defined in ast.runa).
Constant AST_AI_ANNOTATION as Integer is 7000

Note: Token type constants. These match the canonical lexer token types so the
Note: annotation parser reads the same token stream every other parser sees.
Constant TOKEN_EOF as Integer is 0
Constant TOKEN_NEWLINE as Integer is 10
Constant TOKEN_STRING_LITERAL as Integer is 100
Constant TOKEN_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 150
Constant TOKEN_COLON as Integer is 206
Constant TOKEN_AT as Integer is 653

Note: Parser error-type code (PARSING). The diagnostics engine assigns its own
Note: internal phase/category; this constant labels annotation parse failures.
Constant PARSE_ERROR_ANNOTATION as Integer is 2001

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotation Keyword Recognition
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "annotation_kind_for_name" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Map an annotation keyword string to its annotation kind constant.

    Parameters:
      name - Pointer to the annotation keyword string (the identifier that
             immediately follows the opening "@").

    Returns:
      The matching ANNOTATION_* kind constant, or 0 if the keyword is not a
      recognized annotation block.

    The recognized set is the complete annotation block vocabulary from the
    Runa annotation system specification.
    :End Note

    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_reasoning be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Reasoning"
    If is_reasoning is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_REASONING
    End If

    Let is_impl be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Implementation"
    If is_impl is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_IMPLEMENTATION
    End If

    Let is_uncertainty be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Uncertainty"
    If is_uncertainty is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_UNCERTAINTY
    End If

    Let is_req_clar be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Request_Clarification"
    If is_req_clar is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_REQUEST_CLARIFICATION
    End If

    Let is_knowledge be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "KnowledgeReference"
    If is_knowledge is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_KNOWLEDGE_REFERENCE
    End If

    Let is_testcases be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "TestCases"
    If is_testcases is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_TEST_CASES
    End If

    Let is_resource be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Resource_Constraints"
    If is_resource is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_RESOURCE_CONSTRAINTS
    End If

    Let is_security be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Security_Scope"
    If is_security is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_SECURITY_SCOPE
    End If

    Let is_exec be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Execution_Model"
    If is_exec is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_EXECUTION_MODEL
    End If

    Let is_perf be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Performance_Hints"
    If is_perf is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_PERFORMANCE_HINTS
    End If

    Let is_progress be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Progress"
    If is_progress is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_PROGRESS
    End If

    Let is_feedback be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Feedback"
    If is_feedback is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_FEEDBACK
    End If

    Let is_trans be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Translation_Note"
    If is_trans is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_TRANSLATION_NOTE
    End If

    Let is_errh be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Error_Handling"
    If is_errh is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_ERROR_HANDLING
    End If

    Let is_task be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Task"
    If is_task is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_TASK
    End If

    Let is_reqs be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Requirements"
    If is_reqs is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_REQUIREMENTS
    End If

    Let is_verify be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Verify"
    If is_verify is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_VERIFY
    End If

    Let is_request be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Request"
    If is_request is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_REQUEST
    End If

    Let is_context be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Context"
    If is_context is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_CONTEXT
    End If

    Let is_collab be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Collaboration"
    If is_collab is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_COLLABORATION
    End If

    Let is_iter be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Iteration"
    If is_iter is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_ITERATION
    End If

    Let is_clar be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Clarification"
    If is_clar is equal to 1:
        Return ANNOTATION_CLARIFICATION
    End If

    Return 0  Note: Not a recognized annotation keyword
End Process

Process called "annotation_kind_to_string" takes kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Map an annotation kind constant back to its canonical keyword string.

    Parameters:
      kind - An ANNOTATION_* kind constant.

    Returns:
      Pointer to the canonical keyword string. Returns the literal "Unknown"
      for an unrecognized kind so callers always receive a usable string.
    :End Note

    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_REASONING:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Reasoning"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_IMPLEMENTATION:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Implementation"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_UNCERTAINTY:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Uncertainty"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_REQUEST_CLARIFICATION:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Request_Clarification"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_KNOWLEDGE_REFERENCE:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "KnowledgeReference"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_TEST_CASES:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "TestCases"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_RESOURCE_CONSTRAINTS:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Resource_Constraints"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_SECURITY_SCOPE:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Security_Scope"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_EXECUTION_MODEL:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Execution_Model"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_PERFORMANCE_HINTS:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Performance_Hints"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_PROGRESS:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Progress"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_FEEDBACK:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Feedback"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_TRANSLATION_NOTE:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Translation_Note"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_ERROR_HANDLING:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Error_Handling"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_TASK:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Task"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_REQUIREMENTS:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Requirements"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_VERIFY:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Verify"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_REQUEST:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Request"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_CONTEXT:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Context"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_COLLABORATION:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Collaboration"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_ITERATION:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Iteration"
    End If
    If kind is equal to ANNOTATION_CLARIFICATION:
        Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Clarification"
    End If

    Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Unknown"
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotation Block Detection
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "parser_at_annotation_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Determine whether the parser is positioned at the start of an annotation
    block opener.

    Parameters:
      parser - Pointer to ParserState.

    Returns:
      The annotation kind constant if the current token is "@" and the next
      token is a recognized annotation keyword (and not "End"). Returns 0
      otherwise (this is a non-destructive lookahead; no tokens are consumed).
    :End Note

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let current_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser

    If current_token is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let token_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with current_token

    If token_type is not equal to TOKEN_AT:
        Return 0  Note: Not an annotation marker
    End If

    Note: Peek at the keyword token that follows "@".
    Let keyword_token be proc parser_peek_token from Parser with parser, 1

    If keyword_token is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let keyword_value be proc token_get_value from Parser with keyword_token

    If keyword_value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: "@End <Keyword>" is a terminator, not an opener.
    Let is_end be proc string_equals from StringCore with keyword_value, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "End"
    If is_end is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Resolve the keyword to a recognized annotation kind.
    Let kind be proc annotation_kind_for_name with keyword_value
    Return kind
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotation Block Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "parse_annotation_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Parse a single annotation block into an AST annotation node.

    Parameters:
      parser - Pointer to ParserState positioned at the opening "@" of the
               annotation block.

    Returns:
      Pointer to an AST_AI_ANNOTATION node on success. Returns 0 on a parse
      error (not an annotation opener, unrecognized keyword, or an
      unterminated block missing its "@End <Keyword>" closer). On error the
      failure is reported through the parser's diagnostics engine.

    Grammar:
      annotation_block := "@" KEYWORD [":"] CONTENT* "@" "End" KEYWORD
      where KEYWORD is one recognized annotation keyword and CONTENT is any
      sequence of tokens up to the matching terminator.

    The resulting node carries:
      - node_type  = AST_AI_ANNOTATION
      - value      = the annotation keyword name string
      - value_type = the annotation kind constant
      - metadata   = the captured content text string (offset 56)
      - line/column = the source position of the opening "@"
    :End Note

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Confirm we are at an annotation opener and capture its kind.
    Let current_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser

    If current_token is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let open_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with current_token

    If open_type is not equal to TOKEN_AT:
        Return 0  Note: Not an annotation block
    End If

    Let open_line be proc token_get_line from Parser with current_token
    Let open_column be proc token_get_column from Parser with current_token

    Note: Consume the opening "@".
    proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser

    Note: Read the annotation keyword.
    Let keyword_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser

    If keyword_token is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, PARSE_ERROR_ANNOTATION, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Annotation marker '@' not followed by an annotation keyword", open_line, open_column
        Return 0
    End If

    Let keyword_value be proc token_get_value from Parser with keyword_token

    Let kind be proc annotation_kind_for_name with keyword_value

    If kind is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, PARSE_ERROR_ANNOTATION, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Unrecognized annotation keyword", open_line, open_column
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Consume the annotation keyword.
    proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser

    Note: Consume the optional ":" that separates the keyword from the body.
    Let after_keyword be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser

    If after_keyword is not equal to 0:
        Let ak_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with after_keyword

        If ak_type is equal to TOKEN_COLON:
            proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        End If
    End If

    Note: Capture the body content up to the matching "@End <Keyword>".
    Note: Content is rebuilt from token value strings separated by single
    Note: spaces; newline tokens are emitted as line breaks so multi-line
    Note: bodies preserve their structure. The scan terminates only on a
    Note: matching "@End <Keyword>" terminator. Encountering EOF first means
    Note: the block is unterminated -> parse error.
    Let content be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with ""
    Let need_separator be 0
    Let terminated be 0

    Loop forever:
        Let body_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser

        If body_token is equal to 0:
            Break  Note: End of stream -> unterminated
        End If

        Let body_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with body_token

        If body_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF:
            Break  Note: Explicit EOF -> unterminated
        End If

        Note: Detect the "@End <Keyword>" terminator.
        If body_type is equal to TOKEN_AT:
            Let next_token be proc parser_peek_token from Parser with parser, 1
            Let next_value be 0

            If next_token is not equal to 0:
                Set next_value to proc token_get_value from Parser with next_token
            End If

            Let next_is_end be 0

            If next_value is not equal to 0:
                Set next_is_end to proc string_equals from StringCore with next_value, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "End"
            End If

            If next_is_end is equal to 1:
                Note: Consume "@" and "End".
                proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
                proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser

                Note: The terminator keyword must match the opener keyword.
                Let close_keyword_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
                Let close_kind be 0

                If close_keyword_token is not equal to 0:
                    Let close_value be proc token_get_value from Parser with close_keyword_token
                    Set close_kind to proc annotation_kind_for_name with close_value
                    proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
                End If

                If close_kind is not equal to kind:
                    proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, PARSE_ERROR_ANNOTATION, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Annotation closer keyword does not match opener", open_line, open_column
                    Return 0
                End If

                Set terminated to 1
                Break
            End If
        End If

        Note: Newline tokens become explicit line breaks in the content.
        If body_type is equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE:
            Set content to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with content, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "\n"
            Set need_separator to 0
            proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        Otherwise:
            Let body_value be proc token_get_value from Parser with body_token

            If body_value is not equal to 0:
                If need_separator is equal to 1:
                    Set content to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with content, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with " "
                End If

                Set content to proc string_concat from StringPrimitive with content, body_value
                Set need_separator to 1
            End If

            proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        End If
    End While

    Note: An unterminated block is a hard parse error.
    If terminated is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, PARSE_ERROR_ANNOTATION, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Unterminated annotation block: missing '@End' closer", open_line, open_column
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Build the annotation AST node.
    Let node be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_AI_ANNOTATION, open_line, open_column

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0  Note: Allocation failed
    End If

    Note: value = annotation keyword name; value_type = annotation kind.
    Let name_string be proc annotation_kind_to_string with kind
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with node, name_string, kind

    Note: metadata (offset 56) = captured content text.
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with node, 56, content

    Return node
End Process

Process called "parse_annotation_blocks" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Parse a run of zero or more consecutive annotation blocks.

    Parameters:
      parser - Pointer to ParserState.

    Returns:
      Pointer to a List of AST_AI_ANNOTATION nodes (possibly empty). Returns 0
      only on a parse error inside one of the blocks; an empty run (no
      annotations present) returns an empty List, never 0.

    Annotations frequently appear in sequence above a single construct (for
    example an @Reasoning block followed by an @Implementation block). This
    walks every consecutive annotation block, tolerating intervening newline
    tokens, and collects each parsed node in order.
    :End Note

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let blocks be proc create from List

    Loop forever:
        Note: Skip any newline tokens between annotation blocks.
        Let between_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser

        If between_token is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If

        Let between_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with between_token

        If between_type is equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE:
            proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        Otherwise:
            Note: Stop unless another annotation block opener is present.
            Let kind be proc parser_at_annotation_block with parser

            If kind is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If

            Let node be proc parse_annotation_block with parser

            If node is equal to 0:
                Return 0  Note: Propagate the parse error.
            End If

            proc append from List with blocks, node
        End If
    End While

    Return blocks
End Process

Process called "attach_annotations_to_node" takes target_node as Integer, annotations as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Attach a list of parsed annotation nodes to the construct they govern.

    Parameters:
      target_node  - Pointer to the construct AST node the annotations
                     precede (a process, type, statement, etc.).
      annotations  - Pointer to a List of AST_AI_ANNOTATION nodes (as produced
                     by parse_annotation_blocks).

    Returns:
      1 on success, 0 if the target node is null.

    Each annotation node is recorded as a child of the target construct so
    that downstream tooling can locate the intent that governs a given
    construct by walking its children.
    :End Note

    If target_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If annotations is equal to 0:
        Return 1  Note: Nothing to attach is success.
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with annotations
    Let i be 0

    Loop forever:
        If i is greater than or equal to count:
            Break
        End If

        Let annotation_node be proc get from List with annotations, i

        If annotation_node is not equal to 0:
            proc ast_node_add_child from AST with target_node, annotation_node
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotation Node Accessors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "annotation_node_get_kind" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Get the annotation kind constant from an annotation AST node.

    Parameters:
      node - Pointer to an AST_AI_ANNOTATION node.

    Returns:
      The annotation kind constant (stored in value_type), or 0 if the node is
      null or not an annotation node.
    :End Note

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with node

    If node_type is not equal to AST_AI_ANNOTATION:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let kind be proc ast_node_get_value_type from AST with node
    Return kind
End Process

Process called "annotation_node_get_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Get the annotation keyword name string from an annotation AST node.

    Parameters:
      node - Pointer to an AST_AI_ANNOTATION node.

    Returns:
      Pointer to the annotation keyword name string (stored in value), or 0 if
      the node is null or not an annotation node.
    :End Note

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with node

    If node_type is not equal to AST_AI_ANNOTATION:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let name be proc ast_node_get_value from AST with node
    Return name
End Process

Process called "annotation_node_get_content" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Get the captured content text from an annotation AST node.

    Parameters:
      node - Pointer to an AST_AI_ANNOTATION node.

    Returns:
      Pointer to the captured content string (stored in the node's metadata
      field at offset 56), or 0 if the node is null or not an annotation node.
    :End Note

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with node

    If node_type is not equal to AST_AI_ANNOTATION:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: metadata field lives at offset 56 of the base ASTNode.
    Let content be proc memory_get_qword from Layout with node, 56
    Return content
End Process
